===Etymology===
From {{L.}} ''rhinoceros'', ''[[rhinocerontas]]'', from {{Gr.}} [[ῥίς]] (rino) nose, + [[κέρας]] (keras) horn

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=rhinoceros|'''rhinoceros''', '''[[rhinoceroses]]''', or '''[[rhinocerotes]]'''}}

# Any of several large [[herbivorous]] [[pachyderm]]s native to Africa and Asia of the family ''[[Rhinocerotidae]]'', with one or two [[horn]]s on their [[snout]]s. Short form: '''[[rhino]]'''

====Usage notes====
*In natural history, the plural ''rhinoceros'' is often used, in the same way that the singular of the names of many wild animals is often used in natural history as the plural (compare "gazelle", "elephant", etc).
*The supposed plurals ''rhinoceri'' and ''rhinoceroi'' do not exist in English.
*The plural form ''rhinocerotes'' is archaic.

